                    Welcome to <b>IdentityToken</b>! But wait, what is it? Is it a token sale? an ICO? an NFT? <br />
                    <br />
                    <b>NO</b>, we are not selling anything!
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <b>IdentityToken</b> is an idea, the idea of owning your identity and bringing it with you. Eliminating the need for custodians and middlemen for managing your identity. Eliminating passwords and centralized databases for authentication.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    Using the <b>Cardano</b> Blockchain and its Native Asset feature. We are proud to present our proof of concept of the <b>IdentityToken</b> as a means of authentication.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    In this page, you will be able to mint your own <b>IdentityToken</b> right in your browser. Without centralized servers and you will be able to receive it directly in your wallet as a <b>Cardano</b> native asset. 
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    Once minted, you will be able to prove your identity to services that will support the protocol. We provide a demo chat-service to show an example on how it could be used. But <b>IdentityToken</b> could be utilized for so much more use-cases.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    Potential Applications: 
                        <b>NFT Ownership Tracking</b>,
                        <b>Cardano Social Media Profile</b>,
                        <b>Linking third-party service (Discord, Twitter) to your Cardano Wallet</b>,
                    the possibilities are endless!
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    We will provide a technical white-paper in the future (coming soonâ„¢), detailing the rules of the <b>IdentityToken</b> as a protocol and how to use it.
                    In the meantime you can explore out <a href="https://github.com/ADAPhilippines/IdentityToken" target="_blank"><b class="underline">GitHub</b></a> page.
                    We think it could compliment other authentication protocols like the <a href="https://oauth.net/2/" target="_blank"><b class="underline">OAuth2</b></a> protocol.
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    Finally, We don't expect <b>IdentityToken</b> to suddenly be the standard of authentication, we are simply sharing an idea. A glimpse of a decentralized future. A showcase of what <b>Cardano</b> can do, even without smart-contracts!
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    If you would like to know more, please <a href="mailto:dev.adaph.io@outlook.com"><b class="underline">contact us</b></a>.
                </p>
